I am thinking about to do like this. the flow be:

# step 1
user is asking for UI changes

# step 2
AI brain received, and call bun-server to fire "updating" message via websocket to playground client side.

# step 3
playground client side received the "updating" message, will show a small dialog message of "AI is cooking the UI changes...[spinning loading icon]" on top middle of screen.
this small dialog message should be non-blocking to UI (So it will not create an overlay that blocking user actions)

# step 4
actually meanwhile of step 3, AI may ask for changes (in chat view) or just do the change processing.
AI may send live commands as it is now. Playground side may apply the live commands. (While the updating message still on screen)
playground is also keep the normal collecting state as well.
user can interact normally.

# step 5
AI will eventually updating shadow sources.
After updated shadow sources done, AI will go to pre-deploy step.

# step 6
AI will call bun-server to fire "pre-deploy" message via websocket to playground client side.
AI need check file synced state again, then think to applying the state to the new UI if applicable (If the scenario is creating a totally different UI, so original state didnt matter anymore, then no need to do this).
This step is to make sure that latest state is also reflecting in UI.
AI will then call bun-server to send a "reload" message via websocket to playground client side.

# step 7
playground side received the "pre-deploy" message, it will dismiss the "updating" message dialog.
but then playground will wear a very thin overlay (so blocking user further interaction),
and on top middle of screen showing a message of "AI is deploying the UI changes...[spin loading icon]"

# step 8
Basically AI no need to wait other stuff, it just continue to finished its state updating UI job.

# step 9
After AI finished the final state updating of shadow UI.
AI trigger the deploy.sh script to swap the UI.
then AI call bun-server to fire "reload" message via websocket to playground client side.

# step 10
playground side received the "reload" message, reload the playground to showing the new UI.





